# Component Implementation Workflow

## 1. Propose Components Before Implementation

> **STOP AND WAIT**: You MUST present a proposal and receive explicit approval before writing ANY implementation code.

**ALWAYS** present the Kendo UI components you plan to use and wait for user approval before implementing.

### Proposal Format

Before coding, present:

```markdown
## Proposed Kendo Components

| UI Element | Kendo Component | Module |
|---|-----|-----|
| Search input | kendo-textbox | InputsModule |
| Submit button | kendoButton | ButtonsModule |
| Data table | kendo-grid | GridModule |

**Kendo Documentation:**
- [TextBox](https://www.telerik.com/kendo-angular-ui/components/inputs/textbox)
- [Button](https://www.telerik.com/kendo-angular-ui/components/buttons/button)

Shall I proceed with this implementation?
```

**Do NOT proceed until user explicitly approves.**

## 2. Icon Management

> **BEFORE using ANY icon**, check `assets/tokens/vdc-icons.json` first.

### Icon Verification Checklist

For EVERY icon you use:
- [ ] Search vdc-icons.json for the icon name (e.g., `fa-xmark`)
- [ ] If NOT found, add it BEFORE using it in code
- [ ] Keep a running list of icons used during implementation

When using a new icon that is NOT in `assets/tokens/vdc-icons.json`:

1. **STOP** - Do not use the icon yet
2. **Add the icon** to `assets/tokens/vdc-icons.json` following the existing format:

```json
{
  "name": "Icon Name",
  "purpose": "What the icon represents",
  "entity": null,
  "category": "Navigation|VDC Entities|VDC Actions|Context & Users|Status|Other",
  "variants": [
    { "label": "Current", "fontAwesome": "fa-regular fa-icon-name", "isProduction": false }
  ]
}
```

3. **Then** use the icon in your implementation

## 3. Component Documentation

> **Document incrementally** - Update components.json as you make design decisions, not at the end.

After implementing a VDC component wrapper, update `assets/data/components.json`:

```json
{
  "name": "VdcComponentName",
  "slug": "vdc-component-name",
  "description": "What this component does",
  "kendoBase": ["kendo-base-component"],
  "kendoDocs": "https://www.telerik.com/kendo-angular-ui/components/...",
  "templateChanges": [
    "Custom prefix template for search icon",
    "Modified separator icon"
  ],
  "status": "draft",
  "category": "Navigation|Actions|Inputs|Data Display|Overlays"
}
```

### Required Fields

- `name` - PascalCase component name (e.g., VdcSideNav)
- `slug` - kebab-case selector (e.g., vdc-side-nav)
- `description` - Brief description of purpose
- `kendoBase` - Array of underlying Kendo components used
- `kendoDocs` - Link to primary Kendo documentation
- `status` - "draft" or "ready"
- `category` - Component category

### Optional Fields

- `templateChanges` - Array of VDC-specific template modifications
- `designDecisions` - Array of design decisions made during mockup

## 4. Design Decision Documentation

When making design decisions during mockup implementation, document them:

```json
{
  "designDecisions": [
    "Used fa-angles-left/right for collapse instead of sidebar icons for better visibility",
    "Breadcrumb separator changed from chevron-right to arrow-right per user preference"
  ]
}
```

## Workflow Summary

```
User Request
    ↓
Analyze Requirements
    ↓
Propose Kendo Components → Wait for Approval
    ↓
Check for New Icons → Add to vdc-icons.json if needed
    ↓
Implement Component
    ↓
Update components.json with docs and decisions
    ↓
Complete
```